The Nkomazi Municipality in Mpumalanga appealing for a greater law enforcement presence at the border before the situation spirals out of control. Courtesy of #DStv403 MALELANE - The Nkomazi Municipality in Mpumalanga is appealing for help as it battles illegal border crossings on two fronts. It wants a greater law enforcement presence at the border before the situation spirals out of control. READ: COVID-19 border closures on land and sea Residents say people cross over the border from Eswatini in desperation for basic necessities like food and medical assistance. A similar situation is unfolding at the Mozambican border. READ: Eswatini to intensify COVID-19 lockdown regulations Illegal immigrants are using this path to cross over to Mozambique and back into South Africa. The municipality says this issue is a huge concern for them and is placing the lives of many in danger, especially now with the coronavirus pandemic. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.